I"<p><strong>Abstract</strong></p>

<p>Matrix manipulation is a crucial skill in modern ML practices. In this blog I’ll collect some of the most known transformations/operations that I have encountered and used.</p>

<h2 id="content">Content:</h2>
<ol>
  <li><a href="#the-passpartout">The Passepartout</a></li>
  <li><a href="#references">References</a></li>
</ol>

<h2 id="the-passepartout">The Passepartout:</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
\[\frac{\partial b^\intercal a}{\partial a} = b\]
  </li>
  <li>
\[\frac{\partial a^\intercal A a}{\partial a} = (A^\intercal + A)a\]
  </li>
  <li>
\[\frac{\partial \log (\det A) }{\partial A}= (A^{-1})^\intercal\]
  </li>
  <li>
\[\frac{\partial tr(BA)}{\partial A}= B^\intercal\]
  </li>
  <li>
\[\frac{\partial A^{-1}}{\partial \alpha} = - A^{-1} \frac{\partial A}{\partial \alpha} A^{-1}\]
  </li>
  <li>
\[\frac{\partial \det A }{\partial A}= (\det A) A^{-1} \;\;\;\; \text{Such a beauty!}\]
  </li>
</ol>

